Detailed Description

This class maintains an entity template, as constructed from its definition file and python scripts.

It is used to create new python class objects and to retrieve static entity type information.

PyObject * EntityType::newDictionary ( BinaryIStream &  stream,
StreamContents  contents 
) const

This function returns a brand new instance of a dictionary associated with this entity type.

It streams the properties from the input stream. This is only used for creating the player entity, and thus only the base-and-client data or the cell-and-[own|]client data is on the stream.

PyObject * EntityType::newDictionary ( DataSectionPtr  pSection = NULL  )  const

This function returns a brand new instance of a dictionary associated with this entity type.

If a data section is passed in, the values are read from it, otherwise entries get their default values.
